OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F411A1777986670
OL,3,C'1 in 15,000': Baby born with rare
OL,4,Ccondition thriving due to life-saving
OL,5,Cscan
OL,7,FThe most common features of the
OL,8,Fcondition include:
OL,10,FSome children with the condition are
OL,11,Fat risk of Wilms' tumour of the kidney.
OL,13,FOther features of the condition
OL,14,Finclude subtle alterations in the
OL,15,Fshape of the ears and, rarely, cleft
OL,16,Fpalate or a congenital heart defect.
OL,18,FTumours other than Wilms' tumour, for
OL,19,Fexample hepatoblastoma (childhood
OL,20,Fliver tumour), occasionally occur in
OL,21,Fchildhood but are much less common.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G8/9
